\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-461\li461\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid5246476 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 What age did you start work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 At - wait a minute love - twelve, half time. At }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313129\charrsid3816264 Musgrave\rquote s}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 . Yes, on Chorley Old Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 And you were a hank dyer weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 No, I weren't - me husband were hank dyer. Me husband were the hank dyer. I worked in the card room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 You were a carder were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 No, I was a jack frame tenter, when I finished up, working. I went in the mill, I learned in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9313129\charrsid3816264 Musgrave\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 
, as a setter on and you've to work yourself up you see. When I left - I left off just - well did I leave the mill - I left the mill before - did I - before - no, after I was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5639861 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264  I left the mill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 You worked after you were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5639861 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264  did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Just a little while, not very long.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 You started work at thirteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 No, twelve, full time thirteen. I went half time at twelve.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 What wage did you get?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Oh - don't worry, we didn't get so much, two and tuppence. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313129\charrsid3816264 
For half time and four and fourpence for full time, setter-on, they called - we worked for the Rovers, the - the jack frame tenter, we like put bobbins on for them and did a bit of cleaning you see, 'til we get moved up
, you get moved up, follow the trade up you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 
You go from setting-on onto card tenting, at Musgrave and from there you went on; the drawing frames and then on slover frames and from there on the fly frames and from there on the jack frames and the jack 
frames worked for the spinners you see. For - they made cops you see, the spinners, they used our bobbins what we made you see for the spinners.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 What did you think about your wage in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Well - they didn't bother so much, it did all right, it had to do.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 What time did you start and what time did you finish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Six o'clock, finish at half past five at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 When you were half time what did you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Part time? Well we worked mornings one week and afternoons the other week
, you see. There was that and another girl against me. I'd go on say six 'til half past twelve and the other girl would go half past one to half past five. Now the week after I would do and she would do my turn. Half time. But full time you went from six 
o'clock 'til half past five at night and we worked 'til one o'clock at Saturday you know. One o'clock at Saturday, fifty-one and a half hours a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 What was the boss like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Oh he were all right. Oh yes, Mr - eeh what -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 How did you get on with the people you worked with, did you like the mill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Oh yes, we were happy together why not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Would you have liked to have done another job or did you enjoy it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 No, I enjoyed the mill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 You wouldn't have liked to have done anything else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 No, not as I know of, not really you know. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 You were in the mill until you finished work altogether?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 'Til I finish - oh yes, and I went on munitions - first world war, yes, at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313129\charrsid3816264 
Dobson\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264  at Bradley Fold. I had - two children then. They
 went to school you know and the lady next door looked after them, giving them their dinner. Yes, I worked there a bit then they put us on night work, you know, well my husband wouldn't let me do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 He didn't like you working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 No, not nights. Didn't like me working nights. He said, I don't work night work - night shifts, so you're not. No, won't let me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Did you have to serve an apprenticeship for your first job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 No, no. Oh no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Did you have a trade union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Oh yes, card room, they used come and collect the card room club, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Did you take pat in any of the things it did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 
No. No. No, he used to come round for our - our money, say Monday, it could be Tuesday, and we used to pay fourpence a week. I think it were only fourpence a week, we paid union money. Now whether it ever went up well - I forget - it could do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Did you think there was a difference of interest amongst the workers, the people you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Really - no, I couldn't say I - no. I loved me work and I liked it, yes, I liked the work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 You don't think there was any division of interest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 No, there's nothing as I would have liked anything - no, no. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Did you think there was a big difference between the craftsmen in the mill and the ordinary labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Well no, I wouldn't say that neither. Not myself now luv because I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 When you started work did it change your attitude to life, did you feel very grown up all of a sudden when you left school and started work
?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Oh well we would be wouldn't we.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 What difference would it make to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Sometimes you got threepence back and me grandma used borrow it off us, that were our spending Money. And I never saw it no more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 What did she borrow it for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Well she'd be run short of money happen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 She was very poor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 She were - oh, you weren't well off, no, but we were all right - we got good food, different than they're eating now.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Tell me about your food, what would you have for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 
Oh - what did we have our breakfast them days? Well me grandma used to make us oatmeal porridge many and many and many a time. The real oatmeal porridge, you know, and then she'd make us potato pie or rabbit pie, for our dinner, this was our dinner
s you know, rabbit pie, potato pie, we'd have tatoe hash. Sunday now - what was left Sunday was always used up at the Monday. Oh yes, if there were anything left over it was put for your dinner at Monday. Now sometimes me grandmother would make us a pan o
f
 hash, what we call potato hash, some calls it - Irish stew if you like. Yes. We were - that way, that were the Monday's dinner. We used call it the resurrection. We'd say resurrection day, we knew what we had to have you know. And sometimes we'd have - m
e grandma'd get some }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313129\charrsid3816264 kippers}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 
 or finney haddock for our tea, but we'd not so much you know, we just got a share - a sharing of it because we couldn't afford good lot but what we had were good. The bread and butter were good. You get - my grandmother always baked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Did she bring you up, your mother died when you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 
Yes, yes. She - a year and a half and - she had to bring us up, she - there were nobody else to bring us up. She made everything. Baked, washed. And we used to help her. Turn the 
mangle, used to have the wooden mangle then, you know, wooden rollers and I used to - she used to say, come on now, the soaked clothes wrapped up and then we used to mangle 'em, what we call mangle 'em, it was called }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9313129\charrsid3816264 squeezing}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264  when they get 'em out the dolly tub and get 'em ready for the mangle, it was called come and squeeze 'em, they were wet, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313129\charrsid3816264 squeeze}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264  the water. And then when they were ready for - ironing, we'd to mangle them. It was a good help to ironing. Oh yes, oh it helps the }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313129\charrsid3816264 ironing}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 , very }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313129\charrsid3816264 ,very}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264  much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Did you all help your granny?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Yes, we helped - we helped me grandma.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 You all had jobs to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 What jobs did you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Well - we used to - we used to do the bedrooms every Tuesday night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Just you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Oh no, me and me other sister, our Nellie.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Did the boys do any jobs?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 
Oh yes, our Jim used to do mopping for me grandma. He - she used to give him threepence, he - you know - he told her. She said, I'll give you threepence if you do me kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 And did he do it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 
Aye, he used to get on his hands and knees, you know, in the kitchen. We'd no carpet, luv, there but in the house part we'd oil cloth all round and a carpet in the middle and a hearth rug and fire irons you know. Oh them fire irons. Oh. We
 had to clean 'em. Put 'em on the sofa, or couch as you would say, we hadn't settee - why, suites then, you know, ordinary chairs, what you sit on, two }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313129\charrsid3816264 rocking}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264  chairs, one at either side - at either side and ordinary chairs and she - we used - to - when we'd cleaned them at Friday we used to have to put 'em over - we hadn't to put 'em down again you know. Oh no, because they're 
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313129\charrsid3816264 frightened}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264  of 'em getting slack you see, we'd have like a little }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313129\charrsid3816264 
dust}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264  ashpan at front and - cover 'e, over with a table cloth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 So they wouldn't get splashed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 And so they wouldn't get splashed and then Saturday morning they was put down. To -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 For the weekend?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Yes. 'Til we clean them again for the weekend but they'd be on the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313129\charrsid3816264 hearth}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264  all Friday night you know covere
d up with a red table - that were ours you know and I think everybody did alike, you know, everybody seemed do alike - covering blooming fire irons up, what do you know. They've laughed at it many a time here, me and Mrs Alcroft as - I said, did you used 
to - yes, we used to cover 'em up you see. Yes. Yes, oh - oh it were great.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Where did your father come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Me dad was - where was me dad born - Farnworth. He was born in Farn - they were Farnworth people, me mam and all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 What job did your father do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Me dad were a spinner. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 What about your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 
Me mother were in spinning place. That's how she got friendly with me dad. That's all as I heard off me aunties you see. Me mum had four or five - four sisters and they all wor
ked in't' spinning mills. Yes. And do you know, it were eight o'clock at night when - when - eight o'clock they used to work to when me mam worked. They used to take bread to the mill and the butter and do it there when they were having their tea. No, I'v
e never seen it, it's what they used to tell us. Me aunties. Eight o'clock. Eight o'clock when my mum and dad - you know what I mean - before they were my mother and -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 What time would they start in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Six o'clock. Yes, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313129\charrsid3816264 luv}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 , they don't know they're born today. They don't know they're born. They're grousing and grumbling, eeh - and we had like that. Anyway I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Your dad was always a spinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Aye. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 He never did anything else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Do you ever remember him being out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313129\charrsid3816264 Well, he was out of work at Farnworth, the mill closed down, eeh I've forgotten him a bit now luv, and that's how he got to Bolton. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 You see, his union would find him this job here. Well you see with us living at Bolton my eldest brother started for me dad, piecer and as he grew up he got what they call side }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313129\charrsid3816264 piecing}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 
. Well when my dad died he got his wheels. The spinning wheel. My - my - eldest brother got them - got his work. He worked at Park Mill, Bolton. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 That was your older brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Which was the house you lived in longest, was it Chorley Old Road?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 How many rooms were there at Chorley Old Road?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Only - well when we lived in Avenue Street, we lived in Avenue Street when we come to Bolton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 That was Chorley Old Road too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 
Yes. Yes. It's agen the Haslams mills what were up for the side you know. We lived in there a long time you see - 'til me dad died. He were buried out of that house, me dad. Number eleven, Avenue Street.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 How many rooms were there there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 There were three. Three rooms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Three up and three down was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 No, not three down. There were only two down but you see it were this way, we'd three rooms. We'd two lots of stairs. We'd a fron
t bedroom and a back bedroom and then there was a set of other stairs and it - it went like the - we used call it a garret, we would like, and it went all over the - well you could have two beds in that room you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 So you girls would sleep together would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 And the boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Yes. And the boys, they slept together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 In another room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Yes. And me grandmother on her own in the back room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Where did your dad sleep then, he died when you were young didn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 
Well he were dead. While there - well he'd have to sleep - he'd have the front room I daresay, no, I'm telling lie, me dad wouldn't - eeh I can't tell you luv, he must have slept in't' front room with lads.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 What about bathing then if you'd no bathroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Oh no, no bathroom. No bathroom. We had a big bath - of our own - a zinc. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 In front of the fire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 At front of the five every Friday night. Never missed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 When did you change into clean clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Yes, weekend. Yes, weekend.
 All clean clothes at - either Friday or Sat - well we put 'em clean on going to bed, yes. Yes, we had our baths at front of the fire. Yes. No bath.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Did your granny bake and make all her own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Me grandma? Yes. And I - I baked and all, I did all my own baking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 When you were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5639861 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 ?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 When I were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5639861 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 
, yes. Used bake twice a week, every Tuesday and Friday. I wished I were baking now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Did you ever grow your own fruit or vegetables when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Did you ever have tinned meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Meat? Oh no, never - we never had nothing like that luv.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Did anybody ever brew beer for your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Brew beer? No, it - we brewed nettle drink - nettle - me brother's wife, used - and she used to sell it for a 
penny for a bottle. Yes, I used to help me brother's wife.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 How did you make it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 
Well - she used get - eeh I don't know, I didn't make it, I used help her to bottle it and - and put corks on and tie it, you know, at top. She used sell a lot at we
ekend. Specially Sunday when - when they'd been out I daresay the men and they wanted a drink at Sunday morning after they'd had too much at Saturday night or the other - of the other sort. Yes, she used sell a lot at Sunday and, you know, all morning at 
Sunday morning and dinner time. Oh it were good nettle drink luv. Yes. She'd buy t'herb - t'herbs - it's a herb drink you know, were beer it were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 So your grandmother brought you up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Did she come and live with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Yes. Yes. To help -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 So your dad would get off to work and your granny would look after you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Oh granny looked after us, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Tell me about your table manners as a child.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 You were asking us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Were you allowed to talk at table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 No, was not. No, we'd have been sent away and we'd have - we didn't need telling. We knew what we had to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Could you choose what you liked at the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Could you leave a dirty plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Well - I wouldn't say whether we did, well - I do
n't think we did leave a dirty plate luv. No, I don't think we did because you had to eat it, it would have been brought back to you, they used to say, if you don't eat it you get it for your tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 And did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Well, if you didn't like it, no, th
ey'd fetch it but - no, not have it. Can I not have a jam buttie? No, you don't eat that you don't get anything. Anyway, they - me granny used go a bit soft you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 How did your grandmother cook, did she have a range or gas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 No, proper range, a fire - with the oven. Oh - they were cooked in there in oven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313129\charrsid3816264 Slower}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264  - slower cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 
Yes, of course. She used to make us toffee, what - you know these days like - when we had anything - treacle toffee like bonfire plot day -, treacle done up
 in a big roasting tin. Oh, cook - me grandma used to cook everything. We didn't buy anything. Not as - not to my knowledge, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Did you have your own place at table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 And we'd to stand luv. 'Til you was so old we'd to stand at table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 How old would you have to be when you'd to stand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 
Well I couldn't just tell you really, but I were - yes, because I know I was standing before I were working. We'd to come and stand at the table. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 And did she make you hold your knife and fork in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 
We'd no knife and fork, luv. Nearly regular. We'd have a fork probably, we generally had a teaspoon if we were eating potato pie, yes, or 'tatoe hash.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Were you very poor as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Well - we couldn't say we were poor, we we
ren't well off anyway. We managed very well I think. According I think. Yes. We'd good food, what we did have it was good and it was always cooked at home. Yes, always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Did you have a lot of clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Clothes? Oh no, we used get new clothes every year. Every year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 When for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Whit Friday, I'm R.C.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Your Roman Catholic are you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 
Yes. And we always got them for to walk in. And new shoes. When our shoes was done, they're only about one and eleven I think then, patent leather slipper
s, I can see 'em now, with a strap on, when they were done they were done. We had to wear our clogs going to church at Sunday morning and me dad used to clean 'em for us to go to church in them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Did your dad help your granny about the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 We did. Oh me dad. Well me dad didn't - just his own jobs. Didn't take -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Like decorating or something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 No, he didn't decorate. The - they used to come in to decorate at them days luv. So long and then your house were decorated. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 When did you have to go to bed when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Oh we had to go to bed early luv, yes, half past seven. Not like these days, I wouldn't like to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 When you were a child who used to punish you if you did anything wrong?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Oh me dad. Me dad. Ooh me dad, me dad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 How did he punish you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 
Sending us to bed. You'll get no tea. Now when my dad come home from work at night - he used get home about quarter to six, they'd done at half past five, he used to work at Park Mill, we lived at Avenue Stre
et, and we had to be indoors, we'd not to be outdoors out of doors, when my dad come home from his work we'd to be in the house. We hadn't to be out of doors or else he'd have soon have had us upstairs
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Was he very strict?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 As - yes, I seen as he 
were too strict sometimes - when - he'd seen her, now you can go and play. We'd had our tea you know, me grandma used to give us our tea when we come home from school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 All the children sat at tea together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 When did dad have his tea then, when he came in at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 
Oh yes, at night. Yes, always his tea ready for him and - and when it were baking day, luv, we used run home, me grandma used to have our flour cakes stood up cooling off for our tea. I bet you've heard that and it's true
 luv. True enough yes, and she used to have us home there waiting and - the black treacle would be on the table, a penny a pound, thick black treacle in a - in a stone jar or the syrup. You know, they syrup treacle, not Lyle's syrup you know, that used to
 
be tuppence a pound. And we used go stores - always went stores, yes. Penny a pound black treacle. And you could have - but - bur - our syrup or the black went on top of the flour cake, not cooked. Well it - it would have took twice wouldn't it, of the bl
ack treacle. So we always had it on the top and they give it - hot, well it were only baking it away you know. Oh we thought it were glor}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313129\charrsid3816264 ious}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264  - now sometimes me grandma, when she were baking, she'd put a few currants in to cake, put a bit of lard in as she were rolling it and we thought - eeh, we thought we were having a picnic, if there was a few currants in.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Did you do anything special on birthdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Oh yes, oh yes, she used to make us a little bit of - of fruit loaf.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Did you have a birthday present when you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Well no, no, no. No. No birthday card.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 She'd make you a fruit loaf?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 A fruit loaf for our - she would - fruit loaf and she }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7209395\charrsid3816264 used}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264  to make a lot of - tell you what, never had to use - waste any crusts, always used to make, yes, bread pudding. Bread pudding of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Did you ever have a birthday party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 No. Never had no birthday party, I don't - I don't remember, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 What about Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Oh Christmas were all right. Christmas we'd have good t
ime. A present then. Oh we always got a present, yes. Now, me other sister, I can remember us - doesn't matter about me going down but I helped the girl to do the table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Tell me about Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 You can read a book. Oh we used to have - what is call it - me dad he always used buy goose. Yes, a goose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 What did you do on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 
Well me grandma used be in a club like and there were a goose and Christmas cake and different things in this 'ere, like, not tinned fruit you know. T
here might be some fruit, say pears or - as - as me grandma could stew, apple, do you know, like that and she used pay two shilling a week to this club every week and there'd be a goose in it, see, potatoes, vegetable, but I don't know how much it were al
together - and we used to take it for her in town and it were called Devine, in Corporation Street. I remember taking it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Corporation Street Bolton?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Yes. Yes. Devine. And we used to go there with this two shilling every - oh there were a lot used to be in and that's -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Was she in a sick club or a boot club or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Were we - were we in any? No. No. Were in no -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Did she pay an insurance club though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Oh yes, oh yes, oh yes. Well they'd never have got buried would they. Oh no. Oh insurance come every Monday.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Do you ever remember a funeral in the family and what it was like when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 A funeral? Oh yes. It were - it were all right. And it -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 What sort of clothes did you wear and who attended?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 
Black, always black. Always black. We always went in mourning. If they couldn't afford them well people would lend them. Yes, it's true. Yes, they used to lend 'em. Well they'd fetch 'em back straight away, you know, after everything was done, put
 away and settled after tea.
