\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 When you were a child do you remember if you kept any livestock for food, like pigs or hens?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Oh no, we never kept - no, no, we never kept nothing like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Can you tell me how many times a week you ate meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 
We had meat? Well I - I should think we'd have meat pretty often because - we used to have potato pie. Now, every - every Monday, I can tell you this, we had what they called the resurrection. And we alway
s had the meat cooked no matter what it were - cooked, me gran - maybe it were half - a - a shoulder of lamb, weren't very dear then you know, and she used to get - a little hatchet she had, and put it and - on some brown paper you see and chop it in two 
and she would put that in - we'd have potato has on Monday, and a big onion, and - and get the meat off as well as she could. It were blooming good too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 How many times a week do you think you'd have meat though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Well - we had that, now we always 
had at Tuesday, now was it Wednesday, we'd have one day potato pie and then she would make a suet pudding. You know, not kidney we never had kidney, we had steak. I don't know whether it would be steak or stewing meat. Well anyway, no matter what it was, 
we always had - steak pudding. Do you get me? Always - we used to have. Now -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 How many more days would you have it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Oh }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7209395\charrsid3816264 well}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 
 we'd have it - mostly Saturday and Sunday. We used to have steak and onions. Steak and onion, we used to have a - more on
ions than those you know, me dad used to have to have steak I suppose, what we had, 'cos we wasn't so well off, and - Friday, we always had to have - potatoes, me granny used to like boil these potatoes up Friday for our dinner, onion and a - a lump of bu
tter. Best butter, used to have that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Did you ever remember seeing your granny go short so that you could have more do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Well I daresay she would luv. Many a time. Did without something. I - I couldn't say I really remembered her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 But you say your dad always got more, he got the meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 
Well he would get the meat of course. And we used to have - well we used to have pan of onions or boiled potatoes or rice pudding. Oh yes, we had rice pudding. Pretty often. Pretty often, rice pudding. The worker. And we couldn't a - afford it you see.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 And your dad always had most because he was a worker?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 We we were satisfied. We're still here, I'm still here, I'm eighty-eight, what more do you want?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Do you remember being punished as a child, and how did you feel about being punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 
Well - yes, we used to be punished - if we stayed out too long. Had to have punishment. Our punishment were this. Me and me other sister and a brother, and I were the least, always put in the midd
le. Sent to bed. Sent to bed, that was our punishment, my dad never punished us hard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Do you ever remember this happening, being sent to bed and how you felt about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 I - - I'll say. We used to be coming down the stairs and said, dad, can we co
me down? And he used to say, I'm coming, and he'd shuffle his clogged feet with irons on, then we used to go up again, and we used to be back in - back upstairs you know, and we used to get it - all the three of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 How did you feel about being punished, did you resent it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 
Well - I expect we would because we wanted to be together and play, you see, well - but we always had to go up bed early. Oh - always bed early.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Who do you think played the most important part in teaching you how to behave and what was right and wrong?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 
Well I think my grandad - me grandma. Oh me grandma. Oh my - my grandma, yes. She taught us all we ought to know. And I don't begrudge one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 You think she was more important than your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Oh she was more 
important than me dad. Though we knew we had to do you know, you know, me dad hadn't to beat us for anything. H'ed only need to look at us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Do you ever remember young grandmother reading?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 No. No, I never did. I never did. No. But I wouldn't know after - I wouldn't know she had. No I don't think she ever read.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Do you remember your father reading a lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Oh me dad, he didn't read a lot because he couldn't read. He couldn't }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7209395\charrsid3816264 
really}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264  all words but he used to say - spell that for me. And then he would make attempt. Don't think me aunt - grandma did read. She had to read when she -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Could she read though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 I don't know. I - I - I don't know whether she read when she were young or not, but she never - never had no time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 You never heard them reading out loud to each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 
No. No. No. No. We weren't - we weren't allowed to pick a newspaper up and read it, never. But me dad used to - if he wanted something read in the newspaper and he used to call to me, just read me that little bit. 'Cos he couldn't read it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 But he could read a little?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Now read it - read it out loud for me, he used to say, that'll do. We didn't have to read a newspaper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 I asked you before how the people showed their disapproval of somebody they di
dn't approve of, do you remember them making loud music or making effigies or anything like that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 No. No. Not against us. No. I don't remember them against us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Do you remember it anywhere else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Well ; probably I'd have heard that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 You'd heard about the tin cans?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 
Yes. And the children. You know, they were - lads you know, but - you know, and they used to - go about with - things in a bottle, and they called it pitch. You know, alight in a bottle. The - the boys that were growing up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 But this wasn't if someone did anything wrong?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Oh no, I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 You've never heard of anyone tin canning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 No. No, not against us. Oh no, we'd nothing of that. Nothing of that against us as I know of luv, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Do you remember if your grandmother voted in the elections?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Eeh no, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Do you think she was interested in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 No, I don't think she were interested, but she - they were Liberals. Dad was a Conservative, 'cos me dad wasn't a Catholi
c. He were Conservative, but me - me grandma were Liberal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Did your dad ever work for a political party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 
No, he never helped, he used to go and vote. Now I'll tell you who he did vote for, and he were a Conservative - Harwood, factory master, he were a big Liberal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Why did he vote for him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 
I don't know, because he said he were a good man, he liked Mr Harwood. I heard him say - I'm voting for Mr Harwood this - now - now, and it was time - now wait, let me get it for you, oh no, it weren
't when Mr Gikll - it weren't when the Labour man were in, it were - something else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Did you ever help with the political parties or take any active part?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Never. We used to go with a Member of the Conservative Club - he is, me dad. I'll tell yo
u where. Chorley New Road. I'll tell you who kept it too. Do you know - do you remember that footballer called - Nightingale - why - not Nightingale, oh the one whose father were a Scotchman. Joe - what were he called - eeh - and he was on Chorley Old Roa
d. Well there was a con - a con - a Conservative club within a little - first - first house from there going up on the hill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 What did your father do in the Conservative club though, what were the activities that he did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Well I don't think he did anything, only go mixing with them. I never knew me dad to do anything. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7209395\charrsid3816264 It's only when there were a voting time that he used to - but he were a mem - that place, and he - his - his mother }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5639861 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7209395\charrsid3816264  - a Bob Jacks, you wouldn't remember him, he was -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 When the elections were on did your father work for the party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 No, he did nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 In those days when you were young some men felt that they risked losing their jobs if they didn't vote for a particular party.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Do you ever think your father felt this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 No, I don't know, I never noticed anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 He never talked about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Because me dad never - he never - went to doing owt like that. He was a member, I knew that because -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 But you don't think he ever felt he had to vote for a particular party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Oh no, he didn't - I don't think he ever did anything - only going there and mixing with 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 He never felt he had to vote for a certain person because of his job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Oh no. No. No. No. No, my dad always voted Conservative, I never }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7209395\charrsid3816264 knowed}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264  him - only I do say - I know once he voted Liberal, because I heard him telling me grandmas I'm voting for Harwood - spin - oh he'd be dead and buried now no doubt.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Did your grandmother ever go out a lot?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 When you were children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 No. Only out - to earn.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Did she ever go out a lot to enjoy herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 
No. No. When she - no. She liked a drink, she'd have a drink in the house. But me dad always took her having a drink at Friday. Always at Friday night, having a drink, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 So she did go out on Fridays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Yes, but his Aunt Sarah, his aunt -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Who looked after you as children when she went out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2833882 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Well we - well we were big you know, we looked after ourselves. Oh then she went then. Oh she used to go with her shawl on her head. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7209395\charrsid3816264 And go in the kitchen you see, in me auntie's kitchen.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5246476 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16455581\charrsid3816264 Your grandmother wore a shawl did she?
